    {
      "id": "PopularPost253297",
      "post_content": "@holgir: Actually, I would say that, if I were in this situation, all my creatures are in a selective quantum state of having shroud. So when do they actually have shroud? If an opponent is targeting something I own, it has shroud. If I'm targetting something I own, it doesn't have shroud, since i can de-equip at instant speed too. I suppose then all my creatures all practically have functional *hexproof*, which is just crazy to think about.",
